2026-02-24 | Check If All Binary Codes of Size k Exist

	Question
Given binary string s and integer k,
return true if every binary string of length k
appears as a substring of s.

	Approach
1.	Key Insight:
	-	Total possible binary codes of length k = 2^k.
	-	We must see all of them.
2.	Sliding Window + Bitmask:
	-	Maintain a rolling integer value
		representing current window of size k.
	-	Use bit operations to:
			Shift left,
			Add new bit,
			Remove old bit.
3.	Use a boolean vector or unordered_set
	to track seen codes.
4.	If number of distinct codes == 2^k,
	return true.
5.	Time Complexity:
		O(n)
6.	Space Complexity:
		O(2^k)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool hasAllCodes(string s, int k) {
        int n = s.size();
        if (k > n) return false;

        int total = 1 << k;
        vector<bool> seen(total, false);

        int mask = 0;
        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            mask = ((mask << 1) & (total - 1)) | (s[i] - '0');

            if (i >= k - 1) {
                if (!seen[mask]) {
                    seen[mask] = true;
                    count++;
                    if (count == total)
                        return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Instead of generating all possible patterns,
we scan the string once using a rolling bitmask.
If we encounter all 2^k possible values,
the answer is true.
This gives a clean O(n) solution.
